[recipe] | #cuisineparadiseMealPlanner 
With our market being listed as one of the 4 popular wet market, we can only go on either ODD or EVEN days basis. So today is my turn again to clear off and top up new ingredients for the week
.
今晚的菜单：咸菜鸡汤搭配麻辣小炒和煎蛋
.
DINNER
🥬 Stir-fry Assorted Veggie such as baby bok choy, sweet peas, carrot, black fungus, prawns and scallop with mala sauce
.
.
🍲 Salted Veggie Chicken Soup
3 chicken legs, 鸡腿
120-150g salted vegetables (咸菜), sliced
3 tomato, cut into wedges
2 sour plums, optional
6-8 slices ginger
3 cloves garlic
1 tsp white peppercorns, lightly crashes
.
Method
1. In a bowl soak salted vegetable with water for about 10 minutes, changing water once or twice
2. Meanwhile blanch chicken legs then rinse to remove any scums 
3. Place 1.2L water in stock pot and bring to boil before adding in all the ingredients (reserve 1/2 of the tomato) and continue to simmer on low heat for 30 minutes
4. Add in remaining tomato and continue to simmer for 10 minutes then season to taste if requires and serve .
.
📝 note
- you can use chicken bone, frame, breast meat or duck meat (duck requires more than an hour of cooking time in order for the meat to be soft) to boil this soup
.
.
INGREDIENTS
I manage to replenish some fresh Ingredients again since today is another “Even” day to enter the wet market. My usual loot includes pork ribs, chicken, seafood and veggies
.
.
BREAKFAST
Bought our favorite Chee Cheong Fun, Yam Cake, Siew Mai and Har Gao combo
.
.

.
.
